**AJO Expression Editor — Personalisation Language:**

AJO uses a **Handlebars-inspired template syntax** processed server-side (at the Edge) before message delivery.

**Basic syntax:**
```handlebars
Hello {{profile.person.name.firstName}}!

{{#if profile.person.gender == "male"}}
  Dear Mr. {{profile.person.name.lastName}}
{{else}}
  Dear {{profile.person.name.firstName}}
{{/if}}
```

**Available data contexts:**
| Context | What it provides |
|---|---|
| `profile.*` | Real-Time Customer Profile attributes |
| `context.*` | Journey context (journey name, node name, timestamp) |
| `segmentMembership.*` | Audience membership flags |
| `offers.*` | Offer Decisioning results |

**Helper functions:**
```handlebars
{{upperCase profile.person.name.firstName}}
{{dateFormat context.journey.createdAt "MM/DD/YYYY"}}
{{coalesce profile.homePhone profile.mobilePhone "No phone"}}
```

**Expression Fragments:** Reusable personalisation expressions stored in the Content Template Library — e.g., a complex language-detection conditional reused across all communications.

**Exam tip:** Personalisation is evaluated at **send time**, not at journey entry — so if a profile attribute changes between journey entry and message send, the most current value is used in the message.
